This paper deals with computer vision applications such as image editing, synthesizing high-resolution images, generating videos, etc. and proposes a novel training method and learning objective for deep generative adversarial networks (GANs) to discover multiple object instances. The paper also introduces a new deep similarity metric to distinguish multiple objects in one image. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning and GANs, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a modified deep CNN for object detection, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses datasets such as MS-COCO and PASCAL VOC, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
